rComments: Did not get anything done during the class time, yet if you didn't go you'd miss crucial TED day points that are a huge chunk of your grade. I learned more in my high school version of this class than from this instructor. Wouldn't recommend this instructor if you want to learn something.

Worst professor I've ever had. Sarah Stanley take an hour and twenty minutes to cover an eighth of a chapter. Her TED days are horrible and unorganized, and skipping class will screw you over because those TED days are worth a ridiculous amount of the grade. I want to retake Psych with a different teacher so I can actually learn something.
